column12: what worked well is that it built quite fast and I had the feeling that I could push and see results immediately. Something irritating that it did was assume that I wanted to test the CI with a simple python http server instead of an angular app even though I explicitly mentioned it in the prompt. I often had the feeling that I was as the whims of the AI and that the only way I could improve the output code is to pass back the error messages, which made me feel helpless (especially when it still didn't work after that). I tried to ask clarifying questions to understand the code better but didn't get far. I don't know how well it did in writing the CI as the steps before that prevented me from running it fully.
